  "content": "<h1 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ”¬ Light-Sheet Microscopy Quantification</h1><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Automated Analysis of Tissue-Cleared Samples</strong></p><p class=\"text-node\">Light-sheet microscopy combined with tissue clearing enables unprecedented 3D visualization of entire organs and organisms. This pipeline automates the complex workflow from raw 2D tiles to quantified 3D cellular data, making whole-organ analysis accessible and reproducible.</p><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ¯ What is Light-Sheet Microscopy?</h2><p class=\"text-node\">Light-sheet fluorescence microscopy (LSFM) illuminates samples with a thin sheet of light perpendicular to the detection objective, enabling:</p><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸš€ Ultra-fast imaging:</strong> 100-1000x faster than confocal microscopy</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸŒŸ Minimal photodamage:</strong> Only illuminates the focal plane</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ” Deep tissue penetration:</strong> Image cleared organs up to centimeters thick</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ§¬ 3D reconstruction:</strong> Generate volumetric data from 2D image stacks</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ“Š Single-cell resolution:</strong> Detect and quantify individual cell nuclei in whole organs</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ’¡ Tissue Clearing Technology</h2><p class=\"text-node\">Modern tissue clearing methods make biological samples transparent while preserving fluorescence:</p><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>CLARITY/CUBIC:</strong> Hydrogel-based clearing for mouse brains</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>iDISCO:</strong> Immunolabeling-compatible organic solvent clearing</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>SHIELD:</strong> System-wide stabilization for long-term preservation</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>vDISCO:</strong> Nanobody-based whole-body clearing</p></li></ul><blockquote class=\"block-node\"><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Result:</strong> Image entire mouse brains, embryos, tumors, or organs at single-cell resolution in 3D</p></blockquote><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ”§ Pipeline Workflow</h2><h3 class=\"heading-node\">Stage 1: Preprocessing</h3><ol class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Intensity Adjustment:</strong> Normalize brightness across tiles and Z-planes</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Channel Alignment:</strong> Register multi-channel fluorescence images</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Tile Stitching:</strong> Iteratively merge overlapping 2D tiles into seamless mosaics</p></li></ol><h3 class=\"heading-node\">Stage 2: Analysis</h3><ol class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>3D Reconstruction:</strong> Stack 2D slices into full volumetric datasets</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Allen Reference Atlas Registration (Optional):</strong> Map mouse brain regions to standardized coordinates</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Cell Nuclei Quantification:</strong> Automated detection and counting using 3D-Unet neural network</p></li></ol><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ§  Allen Mouse Brain Reference Atlas</h2><p class=\"text-node\">For neuroscience applications, the pipeline integrates with the Allen Institute's Common Coordinate Framework (CCFv3):</p><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ“ Anatomical Registration:</strong> Align your sample to standardized brain coordinates</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ—ºï¸ Region Annotation:</strong> Automatically assign cells to 800+ brain structures</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ“Š Regional Quantification:</strong> Count cells per brain region (cortex, hippocampus, etc.)</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ”¬ Cross-study Comparison:</strong> Compare data across labs using standard coordinates</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ¤– AI-Powered Cell Detection</h2><p class=\"text-node\">The pipeline uses <strong>3D-Unet deep learning</strong> for robust cell nuclei segmentation:</p><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Nuclear Channel Focus:</strong> Optimized for DAPI, Hoechst, or other nuclear stains</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>3D Context:</strong> Analyzes volumetric neighborhoods for accurate detection</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>High Throughput:</strong> Process millions of cells across entire organs</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Validated Algorithm:</strong> Based on NuMorph toolbox (Krupa et al., 2021)</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ“‹ Input Requirements</h2><p class=\"text-node\">Prepare a CSV samplesheet with three columns:</p><pre class=\"block-node\"><code>sample_id,image_directory,parameter_file\nmouse_brain_1,/path/to/images/,/path/to/params.json\nmouse_brain_2,/path/to/images2/,/path/to/params.json</code></pre><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Image Format Requirements:</strong></p><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>File Type:</strong> 2D single-channel 16-bit <code class=\"inline\" spellcheck=\"false\">.tif</code> images</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Organization:</strong> Directory per sample with sequential Z-stack tiles</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Naming Convention:</strong> Consistent tile/slice naming for stitching</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Bit Depth:</strong> 16-bit grayscale for maximum dynamic range</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ“Š Pipeline Outputs</h2><h3 class=\"heading-node\">Processed Images</h3><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ“¸ Stitched Mosaics:</strong> Full 2D slice images corrected for intensity</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ§Š 3D Volumes:</strong> Reconstructed volumetric datasets ready for visualization</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ¨ Registered Images:</strong> Atlas-aligned brain images (if using Allen registration)</p></li></ul><h3 class=\"heading-node\">Quantification Data</h3><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ“ˆ Cell Counts:</strong> Total nuclei detected per sample</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ“ Cell Coordinates:</strong> 3D positions of every detected cell</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ—ºï¸ Regional Statistics:</strong> Cell density per brain region (if using atlas)</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ“Š Quality Metrics:</strong> Detection confidence scores and validation statistics</p></li></ul><h3 class=\"heading-node\">Visualizations</h3><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ¥ Volume Renderings:</strong> 3D visualizations of cleared tissue</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ” Maximum Intensity Projections:</strong> 2D summaries of 3D data</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ§  Annotated Atlases:</strong> Cell locations overlaid on brain structures</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ”¬ Scientific Applications</h2><h3 class=\"heading-node\">Neuroscience</h3><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Whole-brain cell mapping:</strong> Count neurons across entire mouse brains</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Circuit tracing:</strong> Map neural projections from viral tracers</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Disease models:</strong> Quantify pathology in Alzheimer's, Parkinson's models</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Development:</strong> Track neurogenesis and brain development</p></li></ul><h3 class=\"heading-node\">Cancer Research</h3><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Tumor microenvironment:</strong> 3D spatial analysis of immune infiltration</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Metastasis mapping:</strong> Detect disseminated tumor cells in whole organs</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Vascularization:</strong> Quantify blood vessel networks in tumors</p></li></ul><h3 class=\"heading-node\">Developmental Biology</h3><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Embryo imaging:</strong> 4D tracking of organogenesis</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Organ development:</strong> Cell migration and tissue morphogenesis</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Lineage tracing:</strong> Follow cell fates through development</p></li></ul><h3 class=\"heading-node\">Immunology</h3><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Lymphoid organs:</strong> Map immune cell distributions in spleen, lymph nodes</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Infection models:</strong> Track pathogen spread and immune response</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Vaccination studies:</strong> Quantify germinal center responses</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸš€ Key Advantages</h2><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>âš¡ Automated Processing:</strong> No manual tile stitching or cell counting</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ¯ High Accuracy:</strong> AI-driven cell detection reduces human bias</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ“ˆ Scalable:</strong> Process multiple samples in parallel</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ”„ Reproducible:</strong> Containerized execution ensures consistent results</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ§® Quantitative:</strong> Extract numerical data from qualitative images</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>ğŸ—ºï¸ Spatially Resolved:</strong> Preserve 3D anatomical context</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ“š Based on NuMorph Toolbox</h2><p class=\"text-node\">This pipeline implements the <strong>Nuclear Morphometry (NuMorph)</strong> approach developed by Krupa et al. (2021), which pioneered automated single-cell analysis in cleared tissue imaging.</p><blockquote class=\"block-node\"><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Reference:</strong> Krupa et al. (2021). \"NuMorph: Tools for cellular phenotyping in tissue cleared whole brain images.\" <em>Cell Reports</em></p></blockquote><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ’» Technical Details</h2><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Framework:</strong> Built with Nextflow for scalable workflow execution</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Containers:</strong> Docker/Singularity support for reproducibility</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Resources:</strong> Optimized for HPC and cloud computing environments</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Standards:</strong> Follows nf-core best practices for bioinformatics pipelines</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"heading-node\">ğŸ“ Perfect For Research In</h2><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Neuroscience</strong> â€¢ <strong>Cancer Biology</strong> â€¢ <strong>Developmental Biology</strong> â€¢ <strong>Immunology</strong> â€¢ <strong>Anatomy</strong> â€¢ <strong>Pathology</strong> â€¢ <strong>Drug Discovery</strong> â€¢ <strong>Regenerative Medicine</strong></p><p class=\"text-node\">Built with <a class=\"link\" href=\"https://www.nextflow.io/\" target=\"_blank\">Nextflow</a> â€¢ Powered by <a class=\"link\" href=\"https://nf-co.re/lsmquant/dev/\" target=\"_blank\">nf-core/lsmquant dev</a> â€¢ Containerized execution â€¢ Originally developed by <strong>Carolin Schwitalla</strong></p>",
